  "text": "# Node.js ESM Loader and CJS-ESM Interop Implementation\n\n## Overview\nThe Node.js ESM (ECMAScript Module) loader and CommonJS-ESM interoperability bridge is implemented across multiple layers: high-level module loading (JavaScript), format translation, resolution, and low-level V8 integration (C++).\n\n## Entry Point and Main Module Detection\nThe entry point ESM detection begins in **lib/internal/modules/run_main.js**. The key functions are:\n\n- `executeUserEntryPoint()`: Main entry function that determines whether to use ESM or CommonJS loader based on file extension, package.json type field, and CLI flags\n- `shouldUseESMLoader()`: Detects if the entry point should be loaded via ESM based on:\n  - `.mjs` file extension\n  - `--experimental-default-type=module` flag\n  - `type: \"module\"` in nearest package.json\n  - Presence of `--experimental-loader` or `--import` flags\n- `resolveMainPath()`: Resolves the main entry point path\n- `runEntryPointWithESMLoader()`: Initializes the ESM loader and runs user imports\n\n## ModuleLoader Class\nThe core ESM loading machinery is implemented in **lib/internal/modules/esm/loader.js** through the `ModuleLoader` class (lines 110-725). Key responsibilities include:\n\n- **Module resolution**: `resolve()` method (line 581) resolves module specifiers using either custom loader hooks or the default resolution algorithm\n- **Module loading**: `load()` method loads module source code and metadata\n- **Module job creation**: `getModuleJobForImport()` (line 241) creates or retrieves cached ModuleJob instances\n- **Require integration**: `importSyncForRequire()` (line 291) handles require() calls to ESM modules from CommonJS\n- **Custom loader hooks**: Managed through `setCustomizations()` (line 201) and the Hooks class\n- **Caching**: Maintains `#resolveCache` and `loadCache` for efficient module resolution and loading\n- **Translators**: Uses format-specific translators for different module types (module, commonjs, json, wasm)\n\n## Module Job and Linking/Evaluation Pipeline\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/module_job.js** file implements the ModuleJob and ModuleJobSync classes that track module loading and linking:\n\n- **ModuleJob** (line 72): Tracks loading of a single module and its dependencies\n  - `_link()` (line 114): Iterates module requests and links dependencies with the loader\n  - `_instantiate()` (line 160): Instantiates all modules in the dependency graph\n  - `run()` (line 262): Evaluates the module and handles evaluation-time errors\n  - `instantiate()`: Public interface to trigger instantiation\n- **ModuleJobBase** (line 60): Base class for ModuleJob and ModuleJobSync with shared properties (url, isMain, importAttributes)\n- **ModuleJobSync** (line 310): Synchronous variant for handling require() of ESM modules in CommonJS\n\nThe linking pipeline:\n1. Module resolution via `loader.resolve()`\n2. Getting module requests via `module.getModuleRequests()`\n3. Recursively linking all dependencies\n4. Instantiating the module graph with `module.instantiate()`\n5. Evaluating with `module.evaluate()`\n\n## Module Format and Resolution\nFormat detection and resolution are handled by multiple files:\n\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/get_format.js**: Determines module format based on:\n  - File extension (.js, .mjs, .cjs, .json, .wasm, .ts, etc.)\n  - MIME type for data: URLs\n  - Package.json type field\n  - Content detection for ambiguous files\n  - Function `defaultGetFormat()` (line 240) and `getFileProtocolModuleFormat()` (line 111)\n\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/formats.js**: Maps file extensions to module formats\n  - `extensionFormatMap`: Maps extensions like .mjs → 'module', .json → 'json'\n  - `mimeToFormat()`: Converts MIME types to module formats\n\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/resolve.js**: Implements ESM specifier resolution\n  - Handles relative imports, bare specifiers, URLs\n  - Supports package.json exports and imports fields\n  - Validates and normalizes resolved URLs\n\n## ESM Translators\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/translators.js** file implements format-specific translators (SafeMap of ~550 lines):\n\n- `translators.set('module', ...)`: Translates JavaScript ES modules\n  - Uses `compileSourceTextModule()` to create ModuleWrap\n- `translators.set('commonjs', ...)`: Creates ESM wrapper for CommonJS modules\n  - Uses `createCJSModuleWrap()` (line 176) to wrap CommonJS with require()\n  - Handles CommonJS exports as named and default exports\n- `translators.set('json', ...)`: Loads JSON as default export\n- `translators.set('wasm', ...)`: Loads WebAssembly modules\n- `translators.set('commonjs-typescript', ...)` and `translators.set('module-typescript', ...)`: TypeScript variants\n\nEach translator returns a ModuleWrap with the translated source.\n\n## CJS-ESM Interop\nCommonJS-ESM interoperability is bridged through:\n\n- **lib/internal/modules/cjs/loader.js**: The CommonJS loader\n  - `finalizeEsmResolution()` (line 1258): Finishes resolving ES module specifiers for CJS packages\n  - Handles package.json exports resolution that can point to ESM\n  - `wrapModuleLoad()` and `kIsCachedByESMLoader` allow tracking ESM-loaded modules\n\n- Cross-references: When CommonJS calls `require()` on an ESM module, it goes through the cascaded loader\n\n## Dynamic Module Creation\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/create_dynamic_module.js** handles dynamic module creation with:\n- `createDynamicModule()`: Creates modules with specified imports/exports programmatically\n- Used for WebAssembly, JSON, and synthetic modules\n\n## Module Caching\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/module_map.js** implements caching:\n- `ResolveCache`: Caches resolution results (specifier, parentURL, importAttributes) → (url, format)\n- `LoadCache`: Caches loaded modules by URL\n- Uses serialized keys for consistent cache lookups\n\n## Import Meta Handling\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/initialize_import_meta.js** initializes import.meta:\n- `initializeImportMeta()` (line 56): Sets url, dirname, filename for file: URLs\n- `createImportMetaResolve()`: Provides import.meta.resolve() for synchronous specifier resolution\n\n## Module Loading\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/load.js** implements the default loader:\n- `getSource()`: Loads module source from file:, data:, or other protocols\n- `getSourceSync()`: Synchronous variant for require() in imported CJS\n- Handles reading files, data URLs, and validates URLs\n\n## Assertion and Import Attributes\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/assert.js** validates import attributes:\n- Validates import assertions (with syntax)\n- Maps formats to allowed attribute types\n- Handles implicit type attribute defaults\n\n## Customization Hooks\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/hooks.js** implements loader customization hooks (Hooks class):\n- Custom resolve, load, and getFormat hooks\n- Message passing between main thread and worker loader threads\n- Hook registration via `module.register()`\n\n## Native Module Wrap Binding\nThe **src/module_wrap.cc** and **src/module_wrap.h** files implement the C++ ModuleWrap binding:\n- V8 Module wrapping for instantiation and evaluation\n- `ModuleWrap` class (line 36 in header): Wraps v8::Module with Node.js-specific functionality\n- Methods for module instantiation, evaluation, and namespace access\n- Linking dependencies via `link()` method\n- Handles synthetic evaluation steps for dynamic modules\n- Module status tracking and hash-based lookup\n- Integration with V8's module system\n\n## Utilities\nThe **lib/internal/modules/esm/utils.js** provides:\n- `compileSourceTextModule()` (line 336): Creates ModuleWrap from source text\n- `getTranslators()`: Lazy-loads translators\n- `registerModule()`: Registers modules for import.meta and dynamic import handling\n- `initializeESM()`: Initializes the ESM loader infrastructure\n- `initializeHooks()`: Sets up custom loader hooks\n- `getDefaultConditions()`: Gets default resolution conditions\n\n## Resolution Flow\n1. **Entry point detection**: `executeUserEntryPoint()` → `shouldUseESMLoader()`\n2. **Module request**: `import` statement or `import()` expression\n3. **Resolution**: `ModuleLoader.resolve()` → `resolveESM()` in resolve.js\n4. **Loading**: `ModuleLoader.load()` → reads source → detects format\n5. **Translation**: Format-specific translator creates ModuleWrap\n6. **Job creation**: `ModuleLoader.getModuleJobForImport()` → `ModuleJob` instance\n7. **Linking**: `ModuleJob._link()` → recursively loads and links dependencies\n8. **Instantiation**: `ModuleJob._instantiate()` → `module.instantiate()`\n9. **Evaluation**: `ModuleJob.run()` → `module.evaluate()`\n\n## CJS Fallback for Ambiguous Files\nWhen a .js file has no package.json type field:\n1. First attempt CommonJS loading\n2. If imports ESM syntax, retry with ESM\n3. Uses content detection in `get_format.js`\n4. Warnings issued for ambiguous module types\n\nThis implementation provides a complete ESM loader that maintains backward compatibility with CommonJS while supporting modern module features including custom loaders, dynamic imports, import attributes, and WebAssembly modules."
}

